name: Womens Jayde 3/2mm Double Chest Zip Wetsuit
description:
One of our highest performing wetsuits for women, now updated with streamlined graphics. The Jayde is crafted from our top grade neoprene, Yamamoto, and lined with waterproof stretch taped seams. Combined with Flaremesh+ on the back, chest, and lower body panels, this wetsuit ensures lasting comfort and warmth, season after season.

THE DETAILS:
Waterproof stretch taping (100%): all seams
GBS (Glued Blind Stitched)
Wind Mesh back panel
YKK Front-zip
Aquabarrier
Back knee emboss
Hex-tech kneepads
Velcro ankle closure straps (included)
Non slip cuffs
Heat sealed cuff edges
Key pocket 2.0: keyloop with mini buckle
Aquaflush 2.0
MATERIALS:
MX4 Yamamoto neoprene
Flaremesh+ in chest and back
Fox Fleece in lower body
TECHNOLOGY:
Waterproof stretch taping critical areas - A highly durable taping is used in the crucial areas of the suit to avoid leaking and keep it flexible and warm.
Glued blind stitching is a method whereby the panels are first glued together and then only stitched halfway through the fabric instead of fully perforating it, which makes the seams waterproof.
Wind mesh has closed cell neoprene with one side of fabric lamination. The outside of the mesh neoprene offers a better protection against wind chill.
Aquabarrier - This is a silicone printing on the collarbone region of your wetsuit. This forms a barrier between the overlapping front-zip panels preventing water from entering.
Key pocket 2.0 - A key loop with mini buckle - An external neoprene key pocket conveniently positioned on the lower leg of the suit. The standard key loop is now equipped with a mini-buckle to release your key with ease while making sure your key is safe inside.
Aquabarrier - This is a silicone printing on the collarbone region of your wetsuit. This forms a barrier between the overlapping front-zip panels preventing water from entering.

name: Womens Furno 3/2mm GBS Back Zip Wetsuit
description:
Get a FREE Nyord hanger when you buy a Nyord wetsuit. Produced in the UK using 100% recycled ocean plastics.

Perfect for you if: You’re a summer surfer who surfs occasionally, or you’re new to surfing.

Balancing excellent value and quality, Nyord's entry-price wetsuit incorporates some high-end features at an affordable price. Made with the same super-stretchy limestone neoprene as our more expensive wetsuits, combined with a fast-dry jersey lining so you can get back on the water faster. Glued and blind stitched seams, as well as taping on key areas of wear, provide a watertight and durable seal. Anti-slip ankle and wrist cuffs prevent water from flushing your suit. 

THE DETAILS:
Super-stretch Limestone Neoprene - Derived from limestone, Nyord's super-stretch neoprene delivers great flexibility and reduces our reliance on oil by replacing traditional petroleum-based neoprene.
GBS Seams - Panel edges are glued together and stitched on the inside. The neoprene is only partially perforated, resulting in a watertight and flexible seam.
Glideskin Neck - Glideskin is a very stretchy and comfortable type of neoprene. It sits snugly against the skin to prevent flushing.
Anti-slip Ankle & Wrist Cuffs - Anti-slip cuffs stay put for a more comfortable fit and create a watertight seal to prevent flushing.

name: Womens ReWired 3/2mm GBS Chest Zip Wetsuit
description:
The best-selling ReWired now features Halo X2 neoprene throughout the upper body. This new neoprene is made from waste scrap car tyres, oyster shells and plastic bottles, and without solvent-based glues or chemical yarn dying. The new ReWired is a huge leap forward in our journey towards sustainability, with zero loss in performance. With new under-the-hood enhancements in stretch through the body and legs, the ReWired feels better than ever in the water.
